<br>
You die.<br>
<br>
Ok now you have a couple of options... <br>
1. You can release your spirit to the graveyard.<br>
2. You can use a Soulstone that you buy from a Warlock.<br>
3. You have a 5 minute period that you can be rezzed.<br>
<br>
I'll take the options in Order.<br>
<br>
1. Release Spirit<br>
Ok, you show up in the nearest graveyard. There's a spiritmaster there. You can talk to him and be able to have him rez you... this will cost you to lose XP though, but sometimes it might be your only option (on the PVP server it's perfectly legit to kill someone and camp their corpse). Odds are though you don't necessarily NEED to do this. If you chose not to, you run back to your corpse, once there you'll get the option to rez yourself. You'll start off with only 50% life. However you don't have to loot yourself, and you can use abilities as soon as you rez. <br>
<br>
2. Doin this rezzes you immediatley... However you have ressurection sickness that lowers your stats. Also you only have 5% life/mana/energy. You'll be really weak and wide open to be attacked by whatever killed you. However, in instanced dungeons in groups this is a good choice if the fight is going bad... you can pop back up, get healed and be right back in the thick.<br>
<br>
3. Rez... this is self explanitory. A priest, paladin, or shaman can rez you. It takes alot of their mana, and has a long cast time, and they only have 5 minutes to get to you. After that you automaticly go back to the graveyard and do the ghost run.<br>
<br>
Any of the options other than having the spiritmaster rez you doesn't cause you to lose xp. Death is still an issue, because sometimes your corpse run can take a while. Also, if you aren't careful, when you rez at your corpse baddies will be close enough to whack ya again. <br>
<br>
The thing you learn to appreciate though, is unlike the &quot;Other&quot; MMO, it's not such a sting. You'll never lose 8 hours of XP grinding, and you'll never lose your level. To me, WOW is such a great game, because it's FUN to play. I don't feel like I'm sittin down and punchin a clock to do my quests, or tradeskill. Hell even if I fuck up and die, it's ok... at most I've lost 1 quest worth of XP. <br>
